'''''A Checklist of Painters from c1200-1994''''' is the second edition of a book first published in 1978 by the [[Courtauld Institute of Art]]. It contains a list of names of painters, draughtsmen and engravers that are indexed in The Witt Library, named after the art historian [[Robert Witt (art historian)|Sir Robert Witt]], who bequeathed his library to the Courtauld Institute in 1952.

The purpose of the book is to provide a list of [[metadata]] on prominent painters, striving in each case to provide a common spelling for the name, nationality, and birth and death dates for Western artists from the early thirteenth century to the present. In the first version, the "present" was defined as 1976 and the list was 40,000 names long, encompassing 337 pages.<ref>[https://rkd.nl/explore/library/127789 A checklist of painters c.1200-1976] represented in the Witt Library, Courtauld Institute of Art, first edition, London, 1978 {{ISBN|0720107180}}</ref> This second edition corrects mistakes made in the first edition, and lists 66,000 names collected up to 1994 and is 557 pages long.<ref>[https://rkd.nl/explore/library/10790 A checklist of painters c.1200-1994] represented in the Witt Library, Courtauld Institute of Art, second edition, London, 1995 {{ISBN|0720121787}}</ref> After publication of the second list, the Witt Library continued to collect photographic material on paintings, drawings and engravings and contains over two million reproductions of works by over 70,000 artists.<ref>[http://www.courtauld.ac.uk/research/photographic/witt/index.shtml Image Libraries: Witt Library] on The Courtauld Institute of Art website</ref>
